---
const stack = [
  "React Native",
  "TypeScript",
  "Kotlin",
  "Swift",
  "Expo",
  "Node.js",
  "Fastlane",
  "Sentry",
  "Git / GitHub",
];
---

<section id="about" class="py-20 px-6 border-t border-[color:var(--color-border)]">
  <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
    <div class="grid lg:grid-cols-[1fr_2fr] gap-12">
      <div>
        <h2 class="text-sm font-mono text-[color:var(--color-accent)] mb-3">/ about</h2>
        <p class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-semibold">A bit about me.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="space-y-5 text-[color:var(--color-text-muted)] leading-relaxed">
        <p>
          I'm a React Native developer based in India. Over the past four years I've
          shipped production mobile apps end-to-end — wireframes through App Store and
          Play Store — and built the kind of native module work most React Native devs
          actively avoid.
        </p>
        <p>
          My favourite projects sit at the intersection of mobile and hardware: USB-OTG
          accessories, Bluetooth peripherals, embedded devices that need a phone-side
          UI. When a stock React Native library doesn't exist or is broken on modern
          Android, I write the Kotlin or Swift bridge myself.
        </p>
        <p>
          I work best with small teams that need a senior mobile pair of hands —
          whether that's a green-field build, a rescue mission on a struggling
          codebase, or specifically the hard native-module part of an otherwise
          healthy app.
        </p>

        <div class="pt-4">
          <div class="font-mono text-xs text-[color:var(--color-text-dim)] mb-3">
            // tech I reach for
          </div>
          <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2">
            {
              stack.map((s) => (
                <span class="px-3 py-1 text-sm font-mono text-[color:var(--color-text)] bg-[color:var(--color-surface)] border border-[color:var(--color-border)] rounded">
                  {s}
                </span>
              ))
            }
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
